<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="563" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1050,1183]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1050,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Danilov" authorityYear="2017" box="[434,560,1051,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kazenasi">
<emphasis box="[434,560,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">P. kazenasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kohl, 1901)" authorityName="Kohl" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[782,1038,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minax">
<emphasis box="[782,877,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">P. minax</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kohl" box="[899,1030,1050,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" refString="Kohl, F. F. (1901) Zur Kenntnis der Sandwespen (Gen. Ammophila Kirby). Annalen des k. k. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 16, 142 - 164." type="journal article" year="1901">Kohl, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having red legs and a glabrous propodeal enclosure, but differs by the simple clypeus, and by the shape of penis valve (as in figs 71–73) (in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">P. minax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the clypeus is acute apically, and the penis valve is simple). It differs from all the other species with a glabrous propodeal enclosure in having red legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893852/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" targetBox="[155,1432,1240,1925]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1435,1955,2010]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,345,1955,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">FIGURES 66–73.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Danilov, 2017" authorityName="Danilov" authorityYear="2017" box="[357,563,1955,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kazenasi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[357,563,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">Podalonia kazenasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[575,638,1955,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[575,638,1955,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype ♂: 66—general view, labels; 67—face; 68—head lateral; 69— mesosoma lateral; 70—mesonotum; 71—genitalia ventral; 72—genitalia dorsal; 73—penis valve lateral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="564" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,427,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[602,690,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="564" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[708,769,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Head</emphasis>
. Clypeus slightly elongate and concave; apical margin emarginated. Clypeus, subantennal sclerite, and frons with dense appressed silvery setae. Vertex, occiput, and gena microsculptured, with irregular punctures; gena with appressed silvery setae. Erect setae pale. Mandible black with red spots medially. Palpi red. Small spot on scape red. 
<emphasis box="[797,917,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Mesosoma</emphasis>
with pale erect setae. Pronotum and scutum finely rugose, more or less shiny, with sparse, appressed silvery setae. Mesosoma laterally and ventrally with dense appressed silvery setae except upper metapleural area with sparse setae. Propodeum finely punctatorugose. Propodeal enclosure glabrous, finely obliquely striate. Tegula red. 
<emphasis box="[919,986,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Wings</emphasis>
hyaline, with slightly darker spot near marginal cell; veins brown; costal vein dark brown to black. 
<emphasis box="[846,899,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Legs</emphasis>
red, except black coxae and partly dark brown hind tarsi. Claws without subbasal tooth. Spines red, dark on hind tarsi. 
<emphasis box="[978,1095,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Metasoma</emphasis>
all red except dark brown T7 and S7 and except black petiole. Penis valve in lateral view crescent-like, with teeth at inner margin; in ventral view without transverse spines (
<figureCitation box="[510,642,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 66 – 73" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1240,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,1236,1934]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 66 – 73. Podalonia kazenasi sp. n. Holotype ♂: 66 — general view, labels; 67 — face; 68 — head lateral; 69 — mesosoma lateral; 70 — mesonotum; 71 — genitalia ventral; 72 — genitalia dorsal; 73 — penis valve lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893852/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Figs 71–73</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,418,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
